│  │ TransportProvider│  │  MediaPoolProvider│               │
│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
        ↓                       ↓                   ↓
┌─────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ ┌────────────────┐
│ AudioContext    │ │ MixerEngine      │ │ EffectRegistry │
│ • PCM stream    │ │ • ChannelStrips  │ │ • Instances    │
│ • Time base     │ │ • MasterBus      │ │ • Factories    │
└─────────────────┘ │ • InsertChains   │ └────────────────┘
        ↓           │ • Metering       │
┌─────────────────┐ │ • Mute/Solo      │
│TransportClock   │ └──────────────────┘
│• State          │         ↑
│• Cursor         │         │
│• SAB writes     │    ┌─────────────────┐
│• Loop handling  │    │ EffectsBridge   │
└─────────────────┘    │ • Subscribed to │
        ↑              │   effects store │
        │              │ • Wires inserts │
┌─────────────────┐    │ • Manages life- │
│LookAheadScheduler   │   cycle         │
│• Beat callback  │    └─────────────────┘
│• Window align   │
│• Loop bounds    │
└─────────────────┘
        ↓
    ┌────────────────┐
    │ onTick callback│───→ Metronome, Clip Scheduler
    └────────────────┘
             │
        ┌────┴─────────────────────┐
        ↓                          ↓
┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐
│ Metronome        │    │ ClipScheduler    │
│ • OSC bursts     │    │ • AudioBuffer    │
│ • Fade-in/out    │    │   scheduling     │
│ • Downbeat freq  │    │ • Gain/fades     │
└──────────────────┘    │ • Seek handling  │
                        └──────────────────┘
                             ↓
                    ┌──────────────────┐
                    │ Speaker Output   │
                    └──────────────────┘
```

---

## 13. How to Plug In a Synthesizer

### Step 1: Create Synth Factory

```typescript
// In /src/audio/synth/synth-factory.ts
import { createBaseEffect } from "@audio/effects/create-effect";

export function createSynthFactory(): EffectFactory {
  return {
    definition: {
      id: "my-synth",
      name: "My Synthesizer",
      parameters: [
        // Define your synth parameters
        { name: "Oscillator Type", key: "oscType", min: 0, max: 2, default: 0, step: 1, unit: "" },
        { name: "Filter Cutoff", key: "cutoff", min: 20, max: 20000, default: 5000, step: 100, unit: "Hz" },
        // ... more params
      ],
    },
    create(ctx, id) {
      let osc: OscillatorNode;
      let filter: BiquadFilterNode;
      // ... setup synth nodes

      return createBaseEffect({
        ctx,
        id,
        typeId: "my-synth",
        params: PARAMS,
        buildChain(inputNode, outputNode) {
          osc = ctx.createOscillator();
          filter = ctx.createBiquadFilter();

          inputNode.connect(osc.frequency);  // CV input
          osc.connect(filter);
          filter.connect(outputNode);
          osc.start();
        },
        disposeChain() {
          osc.stop();
          osc.disconnect();
          filter.disconnect();
        },
        applyParam(key, value, setMix) {
          switch (key) {
            case "oscType":
              osc.type = ["sine", "square", "sawtooth"][Math.round(value)] as OscillatorType;
              break;
            case "cutoff":
              filter.frequency.value = value;
              break;
            // ... handle other params
          }
        },
      });
    },
  };
}
```

### Step 2: Register in Effects Bridge

```typescript
// In /src/audio/effects/default-registry.ts
export function createDefaultRegistry(): EffectRegistry {
  const registry = createEffectRegistry();
  // ... existing registrations
  registry.register(createSynthFactory());  // Add synth
  return registry;
}
```

### Step 3: Use as Effect

Your synth is now available as an effect insert on any track. It receives:
- Audio input (for modulation/sidechain)
- CV-style control via parameter knobs
- Placed in the insert chain like any effect

---

## 14. Key Conventions & Invariants

| ID | Description |
|----|-------------|
| INV-2 | Non-bypassable brickwall limiter on master (-1dB, 20:1, 0.001s attack) |
| INV-3 | Zero-allocation: all buffers pre-allocated at init, no GC in render loop |
| INV-6 | Emergency mute on 500ms+ sustained clipping, silence within 10ms |
| NFR-13 | High-frequency UI bypasses React, reads SAB via rAF |

---

## 15. File Locations Reference

| System | Path |
|--------|------|
| **Engine** | `/src/audio/engine-context.ts`, `audio-engine-provider.tsx` |
| **Transport** | `/src/audio/transport-clock.ts`, `transport-provider.tsx` |
| **Scheduler** | `/src/audio/look-ahead-scheduler.ts` |
| **Mixer** | `/src/audio/mixer/mixer-engine.ts` |
| **Effects** | `/src/audio/effects/` (registry, base builder, 6 built-ins) |
| **Media Pool** | `/src/audio/media-pool/` (15 files) |
| **State** | `/src/state/store.ts` (main), `/src/state/effects/`, `/src/state/track/` |
| **UI** | `/src/ui/transport/`, `/src/ui/arrangement/`, `panels.tsx` |

---

## Summary

The audio architecture is production-ready with:
- **Type safety** throughout (discriminated unions, strict types)
- **Zero-allocation audio loop** (INV-3)
- **Lock-free communication** via SharedArrayBuffer
- **Reactive effects** via effects bridge
- **Modular plugin system** (registry pattern)
- **Proper cleanup** (dispose methods everywhere)
- **Responsive UI** (rAF-driven metering, async media pool)

A synthesizer would plug in as an effect factory registered with the effects bridge, receiving audio + parameter modulation from tracks.

